<br>
Don't know if this has been warned about before...but I will post it anyway for the unaware...<br>
<br>
A guild member was hailed by a toon in EC.....said they were the alt of another guild member...<br>
<br>
After the general BS...the toon asked to borrow a couple items to try them out....This guild member went though the normal questions.......whats my wifes name......whos your other alt...what drop did you get tonight....etc.<br>
<br>
While these questions were being asked....the toon was giving /tells to the guild member he was pretending to be, posing as yet another alt of yet another guild member....and knew all the right answers.....<br>
<br>
Needless to say....once the items were handed over...the toon camped out...<br>
<br>
This has got to be the most twisted scam I have heard about......this not only scams one person...but brings others into the scam without them being aware of the situation. <p>Eholli Rains<br>54th Pathfinder<br>Iradus Lepus<br>Zebuxoruk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucamoman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Camoman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(9/7/01 10:38:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Scam Warning..</span><hr size=1> This whole time nobody was asking:<br>
<br>
anyone know soandso?<br>
<br>
I'd recomend to anyone this happens to to ask your guildies that one question and ask the person on the other end to log on their main toon and ask to borrow items for their twink. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F25><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ufeanan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feanan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(9/7/01 11:37:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Scam Warning..</span><hr size=1> Actually, one of the more devious and thought out bits of social engineering i've seen in eq.<br>
<br>
It happened at like 3am, after we had been raiding all night.  You tend to sloppy when you are tired, had it happened a different time, i doubt he would have pulled it off.<br>
